episodes.title: Blink
episodes.plot: Sally Sparrow must unravel a time-twisted mystery involving the Weeping Angels, stone creatures that send their victims into the past and feed off their potential energy.

episodes.title: Heaven Sent
episodes.plot: Trapped in a mysterious castle, the Doctor must face his greatest fears and confess his darkest secrets in a four-billion-year loop to break through an unbreakable wall.

episodes.title: The Empty Child/The Doctor Dances
episodes.plot: In WWII London, the Doctor and Rose encounter a mysterious child in a gas mask whose touch transforms others into exact copies of itself.

episodes.title: The Day of the Doctor
episodes.plot: Three incarnations of the Doctor must work together to save Gallifrey on the last day of the Time War, leading to a change in the Doctor's personal timeline.

episodes.title: Silence in the Library/Forest of the Dead
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Donna investigate a mysterious library planet where people are being devoured by shadows, and meet the enigmatic River Song for the first time.

episodes.title: Vincent and the Doctor
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Amy meet Vincent van Gogh and help him battle an invisible monster while exploring the painter's mental health struggles and artistic genius.

episodes.title: The Girl in the Fireplace
episodes.plot: The Doctor forms a romantic connection with Madame de Pompadour while investigating clockwork droids that are opening time windows into 18th century France.

episodes.title: Midnight
episodes.plot: During a shuttle trip on a diamond planet, the Doctor faces a mysterious entity that possesses a passenger and turns the other tourists against each other.

episodes.title: The Waters of Mars
episodes.plot: The Doctor faces a moral dilemma when he encounters the crew of Bowie Base One on Mars, knowing their deaths are a fixed point in time.

episodes.title: Listen
episodes.plot: The Doctor becomes obsessed with the idea of perfect hiding and the possibility that no one is ever truly alone, leading to a journey through time that connects to his own past.

episodes.title: The Doctor's Wife
episodes.plot: The TARDIS matrix is transferred into a human body, allowing the Doctor to finally talk with his beloved ship while facing a malevolent entity outside the universe.

episodes.title: Human Nature/The Family of Blood
episodes.plot: The Doctor transforms himself into a human schoolteacher in 1913 to hide from the Family of Blood, creating complex emotional consequences when he falls in love.

episodes.title: Turn Left
episodes.plot: Donna experiences an alternate timeline where she never met the Doctor, showing how different the world would be without his intervention.

episodes.title: The Eleventh Hour
episodes.plot: A newly regenerated Doctor must save Earth from the Atraxi with the help of young Amelia Pond and her grown-up self, while dealing with a damaged TARDIS.

episodes.title: World Enough and Time/The Doctor Falls
episodes.plot: The Doctor faces two versions of the Master while trying to save Bill from being converted into a Cyberman on a massive colony ship trapped near a black hole.

episodes.title: Dark Water/Death in Heaven
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Clara confront Missy's plan to convert Earth's dead into an army of Cybermen, while dealing with the death of Danny Pink.

episodes.title: Bad Wolf/The Parting of the Ways
episodes.plot: The Doctor discovers the deadly truth behind the Game Station while Rose absorbs the Time Vortex to save him, leading to the Ninth Doctor's regeneration.

episodes.title: Army of Ghosts/Doomsday
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Rose face both the Cybermen and the Daleks as parallel universes collide, leading to a heartbreaking farewell at Bad Wolf Bay.

episodes.title: The Impossible Planet/The Satan Pit
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Rose find themselves on a base orbiting a black hole where they encounter an ancient evil claiming to be the Devil itself.

episodes.title: Genesis of the Daleks
episodes.plot: The Time Lords send the Doctor to Skaro to prevent the creation of the Daleks, leading him to confront their creator Davros and face a crucial moral decision.

episodes.title: The Caves of Androzani
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Peri become embroiled in a political struggle on Androzani Minor while trying to find a cure for spectrox toxemia, leading to the Fifth Doctor's regeneration.

episodes.title: City of Death
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Romana investigate a plot involving multiple versions of a count in Paris 1979, which connects to the origins of human life on Earth.

episodes.title: The Tomb of the Cybermen
episodes.plot: The Doctor and his companions discover an ancient tomb on Telos containing frozen Cybermen, which a group of archeologists unwittingly plan to revive.

episodes.title: Pyramids of Mars
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Sarah Jane battle Sutekh, an ancient Egyptian god-like alien who threatens to destroy all life in the universe.

episodes.title: The Talons of Weng-Chiang
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Leela investigate mysterious disappearances in Victorian London, leading them to a Chinese magician and his master, a time-traveling war criminal from the future.

episodes.title: Inferno
episodes.plot: The Doctor travels to a parallel universe where Britain is a fascist state, while trying to prevent a drilling project that threatens to destroy both worlds.

episodes.title: The Mind Robber
episodes.plot: The Doctor and his companions become trapped in the Land of Fiction, where they must face literary characters and prevent the Doctor from becoming its new master.

cast.character: The Master of the Land of Fiction

episodes.title: The Green Death
episodes.plot: The Doctor investigates mysterious deaths in a Welsh mining village, involving giant maggots and a sinister computer intelligence called BOSS.

episodes.title: Terror of the Zygons
episodes.plot: The Doctor investigates mysterious attacks around Loch Ness, uncovering a plot by shape-shifting Zygons to conquer Earth using a cybernetic sea monster.

episodes.title: The Robots of Death
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Leela investigate murders aboard a sandminer where the crew depends on robots for survival, leading to a classic locked-room mystery in space.

episodes.title: The Haunting of Villa Diodati
episodes.plot: The Doctor and her companions meet Mary Shelley on the famous night that inspired Frankenstein, only to discover a half-converted Cyberman seeking the Cyberium.

episodes.title: Fugitive of the Judoon
episodes.plot: A routine Judoon investigation leads to the shocking revelation of a previously unknown incarnation of the Doctor hiding on Earth as Ruth Clayton.

episodes.title: Rosa
episodes.plot: The Doctor and her friends must protect Rosa Parks and ensure her historic protest remains unchanged while a time-traveling criminal attempts to disrupt the timeline.

episodes.title: Demons of the Punjab
episodes.plot: Yaz travels back to her grandmother's youth during the Partition of India, discovering both family secrets and aliens who witness deaths across the universe.

episodes.title: The Power of the Doctor
episodes.plot: The Thirteenth Doctor faces her final battle against the Master, the Daleks, and the Cybermen while trying to protect the fate of her companions and all of humanity.

episodes.title: The Pandorica Opens/The Big Bang
episodes.plot: The Doctor's enemies unite to trap him in the Pandorica, leading to the collapse of all reality and a race against time to reboot the universe.

episodes.title: The End of Time
episodes.plot: The Master returns with a plan to turn everyone on Earth into himself, while the Time Lords attempt to break out of the Time War, leading to the Tenth Doctor's regeneration.

episodes.title: School Reunion
episodes.plot: The Doctor reunites with Sarah Jane Smith while investigating mysterious happenings at a school, forcing Rose to confront the reality of what it means to travel with the Doctor.

episodes.title: The Angels Take Manhattan
episodes.plot: The Doctor and River Song face the Weeping Angels in 1930s New York, leading to a tragic farewell as Amy and Rory make their final choice.

episodes.title: The Stolen Earth/Journey's End
episodes.plot: Davros and the Daleks steal Earth along with other planets, leading to an epic reunion of the Doctor's companions to save the universe.

episodes.title: Face the Raven/Heaven Sent/Hell Bent
episodes.plot: Following Clara's death, the Doctor endures billions of years of torture in his confession dial before reaching Gallifrey, where he attempts to cheat death itself to save his companion.

episodes.title: Flatline
episodes.plot: Clara must take on the role of the Doctor when two-dimensional beings invade our world while the Doctor is trapped inside a shrinking TARDIS.

episodes.title: The Unicorn and the Wasp
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Donna meet Agatha Christie at a 1920s dinner party where they must solve a murder mystery featuring a giant alien wasp.

episodes.title: The Christmas Invasion
episodes.plot: In his first full episode, the newly-regenerated Tenth Doctor must overcome his post-regenerative crisis to save Earth from the Sycorax invasion on Christmas Day.

episodes.title: The Husbands of River Song
episodes.plot: The Doctor joins River Song on a heist, where she doesn't recognize his new face, leading to their last night together at the Singing Towers of Darillium.

episodes.title: Remembrance of the Daleks
episodes.plot: The Doctor returns to 1963 London where two Dalek factions wage war over Time Lord technology hidden by the First Doctor, exploring themes of racism and fascism.

episodes.title: Spearhead from Space
episodes.plot: The newly-regenerated Third Doctor investigates mysterious plastic mannequins coming to life, marking the first appearance of the Autons and the beginning of his Earth exile.

episodes.title: The Brain of Morbius
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Sarah Jane encounter a mad scientist attempting to restore life to Morbius, a criminal Time Lord, using a patchwork body and stolen brain.

episodes.title: The Daemons
episodes.plot: The Doctor investigates apparent witchcraft in a small English village, uncovering an ancient alien being masquerading as the devil himself.

episodes.title: The War Games
episodes.plot: The Second Doctor's final story reveals the existence of the Time Lords as he uncovers an elaborate scheme involving soldiers from different time periods being forced to fight in war games.
